                             colData = colData,

4.2 Global test of the genotype effect, accounting for possible tissue effect.

To perform this test, we compare the Likelihood of two models : one containing both factors (tissue and genotype) and another one containing only the tissue factor.

dds_LRT_Genotype <- nbinomLRT(dds_LbFV, reduced = ~ tissue)
## found results columns, replacing these
dds_LRT_Genotype = results(dds_LRT_Genotype)
sum(dds_LRT_Genotype$padj<0.05, na.rm=TRUE)
## [1] 0
dds_LRT_Genotype[which(dds_LRT_Genotype$padj<0.05),]
## log2 fold change (MLE): tissue H vs A 
## LRT p-value: '~ genotype + tissue' vs '~ tissue' 
## DataFrame with 0 rows and 6 columns

None of the viral genes show genotype-dependant transcript abundance.

# calculate  TPM (Transcripts Per Kilobase Million) 
# (see http://www.rna-seqblog.com/rpkm-fpkm-and-tpm-clearly-explained/)

#1 - Divide the read counts by the length of each gene in kilobases. This gives you reads per kilobase (RPK).
#2 - Count up all the RPK values in a sample and divide this number by 1,000,000. This is your per million scaling factor.
#3 - Divide the RPK values by the per million scaling factor. This gives you TPM

# 1 - divide by length of each gene in kb
rpk=countData2[,2:33]/(countData2$total_exons_length/1000)

# steps 2 and 3:
tpm=apply(X = rpk, 2, FUN = function(x){
  # calculate per million factor
  per_million=sum(x)/(1e6)
  TPM=x/per_million
  return(TPM)
})

rownames(tpm)=countData2$Row.names

5.3 Define a function to plot individual gene

ggplot_function=function(dataset=dds_LbFV, gene="ORF17", size=1, size_title=10, size_points=3, legend=TRUE, xlab=FALSE, ylab=FALSE){
# extract data from plotCount object for a given locus
d  <- plotCounts(dataset, gene=gene, intgroup=c("genotype", "tissue"),
                returnData=TRUE)
# calcul de la moyenne par genotype et par statut d'tissue
means=tapply(d $count,INDEX = paste(d$genotype, d$tissue), FUN = mean)
means=data.frame(means, c("G495","G495","Lb84","Lb84","Sienna", "Sienna", "StFoy", "StFoy" ),rep(c("A","H"), 4))
colnames(means)=c("count","genotype","tissue")
means=means[c(5,6, 3,4,7,8, 1,2),]

# plot the data
  # plot the data
if (legend==TRUE) {  
  p  = ggplot(d , aes(x=d$tissue, y=count, fill=d$genotype)) + scale_fill_manual(values=c("blue", "black", "red","green"), name="")}
else{
    p  = ggplot(d , aes(x=d$tissue, y=count, fill=d$genotype)) + scale_fill_manual(values=c("blue", "black", "red","green"))+ theme (legend.position="none")
}
   p  = p  + geom_point(shape=21, size=size_points, position = position_jitter(width = 0.1, height = 0))
   p  = p  + geom_segment(aes(x="A", xend="H", yend=means$count[2], y=means$count[1]), colour="red", size=size)
   p  =  p  + geom_segment(aes(x="A", xend="H", yend=means$count[4], y=means$count[3]), colour="black", size=size)
   p  =  p  + geom_segment(aes(x="A", xend="H", yend=means$count[6], y=means$count[5]), colour="green", size=size)
   p  =  p  + geom_segment(aes(x="A", xend="H", yend=means$count[8], y=means$count[7]), colour="blue", size=size)
   p  =  p  + ggtitle(gene)
   if (ylab==TRUE & xlab==TRUE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
   if (ylab==FALSE & xlab==TRUE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.y=element_blank(), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
      if (ylab==TRUE & xlab==FALSE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.x=element_blank(), plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}
      if (ylab==FALSE & xlab==FALSE) {
   p  =  p  + theme (axis.text=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title=element_text(size=size_title), axis.title.x=element_blank(), axis.title.y=element_blank(),  plot.title=element_text(size=size_title), legend.title=element_blank())}

   p  =  p  + labs(x = "tissue", y="Normalized count")
   
return(p)
}

5.5 Plot of upregulated in the head

get_TPM=function(locus="ORF1", tpm=tpm, colData=sample_info, tissue = "A"){
  row=t(tpm[row.names(tpm)==locus,])
  tpm_A=row[grep("A", row.names(row)),]
  tpm_H=row[grep("H", row.names(row)),]

  genotype= colData[colData$tissue==tissue,]$genotype
  infection= colData[colData$tissue==tissue,]$infection
  data_abdo=data.frame(tpm_A, genotype, infection)
  data_head=data.frame(tpm_H, genotype, infection)
  names(data_abdo)[1]="tpm"
  names(data_head)[1]="tpm"
  data_abdo_means=tapply(X = tpm_A , INDEX = list(genotype, infection), FUN = mean, simplify = T)
  data_head_means=tapply(X = tpm_H , INDEX = list(genotype, infection), FUN = mean, simplify = T)
  # order factors
  data_abdo$infection=factor(x = data_abdo$infection, levels=c("UI", "I"))
  data_head$infection=factor(x = data_head$infection, levels=c("UI", "I"))
  res=list(data_abdo, data_head, data_abdo_means, data_head_means)
  return(res)
}

# function from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15006211/how-do-i-generate-a-mapping-from-numbers-to-colors-in-r
map2color<-function(x,pal,limits=NULL){
  if(is.null(limits)) limits=range(x, na.rm=TRUE)
  pal[findInterval(x,seq(limits[1],limits[2],length.out=length(pal)+1), all.inside=TRUE)]
}

# import log2 fold
log2Fold=res$log2FoldChange

intervals=discretize(x = log2Fold, method = "fixed", categories = c(-8:3))
# modify order of the factors
intervals <-factor(intervals, levels = levels(intervals)[11:1])
colours <- intervals
levels(colours)=c(map2color(x = 3:1, pal = colorpanel(20, low="moccasin", high = "red")), 
                            map2color(x = 8:1, pal = colorpanel(20, low="springgreen4", high = "springgreen")))
names(colours)=intervals

# corresponding colours
log2Fold=data.frame(intervals)
names(log2Fold)="log2Fold"
row.names(log2Fold)=row.names(mat)

legend_log2Fold=levels(colours)
names(legend_log2Fold)=levels(intervals)
########################################
# Specify colors
########################################

ann_colors = list(
    tissue = c(A = "white", H= "grey"),
    genotype = c(Sienna = "red", Lb84 = "black", StFoy = "green", G495 = "blue"),
    log2Fold = legend_log2Fold
)

#######################################
# plot
#######################################

pheatmap(log(mat+1), 
         color = colorRampPalette(c("navy", "white", "firebrick3"))(50), 
         cluster_cols = T, 
         cluster_rows = F, 
         annotation_col = df, 
         scale = "column", 
         fontsize_row = 3, 
         annotation_colors = ann_colors,  
         annotation_row = log2Fold, 
         labels_row = rep("   ", 108),
         row_annotation_colors = rep("red", 108), show_colnames = F)

grid.text(row.names(mat), x=1*0.785, , just = "left", y=seq(from=1, to = 0.086, length.out = 108)*0.877, gp=gpar(fontsize=3.5, col=df2))
